				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11625089/scp-4207#post-4244739</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 10 May 2019 18:23:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>rua0</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5324586</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I'd suggest using last names in interview logs.</p> <p>For example:</p> <blockquote> <p><strong>Graeme:</strong> Oh, greetings.</p> </blockquote> <p>becomes:</p> <blockquote> <p><strong>Rsr. Vinycomb:</strong> Oh, greetings.</p> </blockquote> <p>It'd help with the clinical tone. Mia could be left as <em>Mia</em> though given how the story portrays her.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
